Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Add the @couscous{100%grams} to a #medium bowl{} with ½ tsp @salt{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pour @water{200%ml}(boiling) into the bowl.

Cover with a #plate{} or #cling film{} and leave to the side for ~{10%mins} (or until ready to serve).

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces. Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the aubergine is soft and golden, ~{20-25%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, place a #large pan{} (without oil) over medium-high heat.

Pick the @mint{5%grams} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}. Use a #teaspoon{} to easily scrape away the peel.

Once the pan is hot, add the @almonds{15%grams} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%mins}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%pack} in a #sieve{}. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat, with a good glug of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the chickpeas for ~{4-5%mins} until crispy, shifting regularly.

Add the @ginger{1}(grated) and @ras-el-hanout{1%sachet} and fry until fragrant, ~{2-3%mins}.

Add @chopped tomatoes{1%pack with onion & garlic} and half the @harissa paste{1%sachet} then lower heat to medium, cover and leave to simmer until reduced and slightly thickened, ~{10-12%mins}.

Meanwhile, in a medium bowl mix @yoghurt{75%grams}, remaining harissa and half the chopped mint.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once the aubergine is roasted, add to the harissa yoghurt.

Stir to coat evenly.

Season the chickpea tagine to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}, adding a splash of @water{to taste} if required.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and divide between bowls.

Top with the chickpea tagine and harissa yoghurt aubergine.

Garnish with the toasted almonds and remaining chopped mint.